A three-man group of   Zentraedi   warriors, led by   Breetai , takes note of this development, and one among them,   Bokay , wonders if they are being abandoned..

description:
Arizona, 1873. Frank Timmons, former soldier and lawman as well as undertaker at Arizona's Gila Flats Territorial Prison, accidentally releases 117 dead killers from Hell. Frank roams the West, tracking them down and trying desperately to avoid his own damnation. Dying in the effort isn't an option. 

If you like DESPERADOES, JONAH HEX or THE LONG RANGER, you’ll love GRAVESLINGER!
name: the Devil's Playground

description: Maureen Raven has been kidnapped and Pete is not happy about it.  On top of this Ransom is getting creative with his newfound interdimentional powers in a way that threatens not only Britain but the world. Pete and his team need to stop him before it's too late, but first they need to find Maureen.
name: Bows and Arrows Against the Lightning

description: The hit NBC television series comes to comics as Chuck Bartowski and his friends are about to take the world by storm—literally! From series co-executive producer Peter Johnson (Supernatural: Rising Son) and series writer Zev Borow joined with artists Jeremy Haun (The Leading Man) and Phil Noto (Jonah Hex) comes an adventure too big for television! In this globe-trotting, action-packed adventure, Chuck will see many exotic locales, dodge numerous bullets, and be tortured by the world's greatest...tickler? Plus a 1 page back-up story by Phil Noto, Captain Awesome's Tips For Being Awesome!
TPB collects issues 1-4.
name: Volume 1

description: TPB collects issues 5-8.
name: Volume 2

description: TPB collects issues 9-12
name: Volume 3

description: 1-800 MICE is an anthropological study of the imaginary city of Volcano Park (where flying mouse couriers have replaced Federal Express), with a soap-opera-styled fractured narrative and a cast of thousands. The story is a cross between Thomas Pynchon, Robert Altman, and J.R.R. Tolkien, and has earned Thurber raves from The Comics Journal, Vice, and The Fader. Thurber's work is sure to delight fans of ambitious comic book narratives, as well as those of screwball comedy and Oz-style fantasy.
name: 1-800-MICE

description: The second in the ABC A-Z set of books, filled with page after page of material guaranteed to satisfy new and long-time ABC fans everywhere! ABC A-Z: Greyshirt & Cobweb explores the world of Indigo City's man of mystery and revealsthrough the sultry eyes of the enticing adventuress just how steamy crime fighting can be.
name: Playing the Mind Gorilla!

description:
Everything you always wanted to know about your favorite alternate-earth super team but were afraid to ask! Peter Hogan and Yanick Paquette present a guided tour of all the ins and outs of Terra Obscura, revealing all manner of information on Tom Strong's buddy Tom Strange and his comrades. Plus, more background info on the ink that stirs the drink, Splash Brannigan! Sit back and enjoy Hilary Barta's delightfully inky interpretation of the liquid sensation!                                     

This book contains two stories:
The Lonely Galaxy Guide
&
Splash Brannigan Conquers the Universe!
name: Splash Brannigan Conquers the Universe!

volume.name: ABC A-Z: Terra Obscura & Splash Brannigan

description: Ten innocent people become unwilling contestants in a game of death. Given 10 bullets and a gun, it's kill or be killed as they're forced to hunt the other 9 contestants! In the dark, horrific tradition of Battle Royale, this is a non-stop adrenaline-fueled tale of pain and terror.

ABC: A-Z is the first in a series of six one-shot specials featuring card-stock covers brought to you by an amazing collection of comic book creators, filled with page after page of informative material guaranteed to satisfy ABC fans everywhere! This initial volume reveals all the secrets and will answer any questions about Tom Strong and Jack B. Quick, along with their supporting casts and gadgets!
name: Tom Strong & Jack B. Quick

volume.name: ABC A-Z: Tom Strong & Jack B. Quick

description: The countdown to the series finale continues. As the heat rises on the cold streets of Chicago, we check back in with the remaining Minutemen who have plans of their own. Is this all a part of Graves' plan - or has the old man finally lost control?
name: "100 Bullets" Chapter Four: Our Men in the Ravine

description: Everything you ever wanted to know about the crew of Top 10 but were afraid to ask! Leni Muller, one of the earliest officers to wear a badge at Precinct 10, reveals the ins and outs of the force as only an insider can. From the post-war days to the present, Leni knows where all the bodies are buried. Also, King Solomon takes a look at some of America's Best...and worst!
name: Badge of Honor: Policing the City of Dreams

description:
The Birds of Prey have suffered a number of traumatic ordeals lately, and they're ready for events to slow down. But before they can rest, The Secret Society - a cabal of supervillains - takes one of the Birds of Prey hostage, demanding Oracle's secret identity as their ransom. The Birds will have to save their friend and battle Deathstroke to defend their leader!
 
And one year later, the lives of our heroines have taken a dramatic turn. Black Canary has left the team to undergo intensive martial arts training in another part of the world, and in her place the Birds have taken on their newest member... the deadly Lady Shiva!
 
Perfect Pitch features the action-packed writing of Gail Simone (Gen13, The All-New Atom), with dynamic art by Paulo Siqueira, Joe Bennett, Joe Prado, Bruce Timm, David Lopez, and many more! 
 
This Trade Paperback collects Birds of Prey issues: 
Birds of Prey #86 
Birds of Prey #87  
Birds of Prey #88 
Birds of Prey #89 
Birds of Prey #90 
Birds of Prey #92 
Birds of Prey #93 
Birds of Prey #94 
Birds of Prey #95
name: Perfect Pitch

description: The second issue of WildStorm's high-octane anthology, featuring a variant cover by Jason Pearson (Body Bags)! Last issue's chance meeting with DV8 led to a painful and resounding defeat for the members of GEN13. This time around, Rainmaker and Burnout find themselves against the same adversaries (written by Jay Faerber with art by Kaare Andrews and Vince Russell) and the odds for their survival this time out are much, much worse. Plus, learn who's behind the mask of the mysterious new vigilante Jet (written by Dan Abnett and Andy Lanning with art by Dustin Nguyen and Andrew Pepoy). And, a reckless Gen-Active learns the hard way what comes around goes around (written by Ben Raab with art by Scott Williams).
name: Battle Lines; Student Bodies

description: The Joker's lovable partner in crime takes the spotlight in this new hardcover volume collecting HARLEY QUINN #1-7, written by Karl Kesel (SUPERMAN: THE MAN OF STEEL) with art by the fan-favorite team of Terry Dodson & Rachel Dodson (WONDER WOMAN)! Don't miss these beautifully illustrated tales of lunacy!
name: Volume 1

volume.name: Harley Quinn: Preludes and Knock-Knock Jokes

description: Comics' favorite family returns in their second original mini-series! Pity poor Zero. It's hard to be the youngest member of the clan. Be it pursuing her own music, dealing with the travails of high school, or indulging in her first crush, the rest of her family has already been there, done that. When the handsome man on campus, Thad, asks her out, Zero is all aglow, until she discovers that his intentions were less than honorable, and her retaliation ends up getting her grounded. It's a tough time, since, despite the family being full of sagely advice about love, the only one that seems to understand is the adorable boy in science class that she can't leave the house to see!
name: Chapter 1

No one has seen or heard from the Man of Steel in this collection from iconic writers Kurt Busiek and Geoff Johns.

As Clark Kent concentrates on his career, the need for the Man of Steel is stronger than ever-especially now that Lex Luthor has returned to Metropolis with his thirst for power fully intact!

Collects SUPERMAN #650-653 and ACTION COMICS #837-840.

name: Fire Power

description:
Terra receives a warning that her very presence in this time era is an affront to the laws of nature.

Terra defends her friends from homicidal eart-elementals.
name: You Can't Go Home Again Part 1

description: The Elemental Protectorates have come to pass judgment on Terra.
name: You Can't Go Home Again Part 2

name: You Can't Go Home Again Part 3

name: You Are Iron Fist . . . And You Are Not Dead . . .

description:
Betta George is still in captivity under Gunn.

Gwen was making out with some guy when L.A. went to Hell and her powers went out of control and she killed the guy by accident and went to find out what happened.

There was a Story with the people of L.A. where a man was warning that the end was near in front of a movie theater when suddenly Hell broke lose and a few weeks later he was fighting and had written on the sign that "Its almost over" even tho he knew it wasn't.

The third story is what happened to Gunn. In the ally way He lay bleeding and dieing (and lacking one eye) when a group of vamps that were watching from afar took him away and turned him to save his life. When he woke up he killed the one who killed him/ their leader and the others told him that they were in Hell. Yet Gunn said that some how he already knew.
name: First Night, Part 3

description:
After Illyria turns back to Fred the battle begins.

As it is happening Team Gunn is standing back and watching, and one of the vamps says that Angel's going to die before they can kill him, so Gunn stakes the flunky and asks if any one else has anything to say.

Meanwhile Burge tells his champions to attack the civilians and to activate the Hagan Shafts which as it turns out doesn't kill any immortal that you want, its for an immortal to kill them self. So all of the lords, except Bro'os who was working with Angel, blew them selfs up.

Then Spider and the lady's show up to help clean up the city. Angel appointed  Lorne Mayer of L.A., they move back into the Hotel, Wes reavels to Illyria that he tried contacting Cordy but all she could do was make a beautiful tree which was quickly destroyed, Conner told Angel they he and Gwen were dating but couldn't touch, and Illyria took Wes's dead body and said "You're staying with me".
name: Chapter Six

description: One year after the execution of Maxwell Lord and the earth-shattering events of Infinite Crisis, the DCU is still struggling to come to terms with its most powerful heroine. Is she a martyr or a murderer? A politician or a super hero? Discover the future of the DCU's most powerful woman in this sensational hardcover collection!
name: Who is Wonder Woman?

volume.name: Wonder Woman: Who is Wonder Woman?

description: Story framed as James MacDonald Hudson's flashback as he stands at the altar waiting to marry Heather McNeil. See how Wolverine earned his role as best man as a Canadian superhero mutated by cosmic rays begins to rampage across Canada.
name: Vows

description: F5, a story revolving around 12 young members of an elite and secret task force, who hide out as Weathermen" or stormtracking Meteorologists, fills the action/adventure void that today's fans are craving! The fans wanted it, they got it! F5 will undoubtedly and immodestly be one of the decade's most action packed and character driven books produced! That "Whooshing" sound was the readers rushing out the door with their copy of F5#1! F5's first mission finds them over the waters of the Atlantic Ocean, as they uncover a true mystery at sea. Scientists and US Soldiers onboard the USS Hurricane have disappeared and all that's left is a damaged ship. Spies have sabotaged a top secret research expedition and walked away with newly found and very lethal chemical that can be used in Germ Warfare! This leads Penny, the leader of F5, and her team on an intense search-and-destroy mission through Europe that ends in Russia to uncover the sinister and diabolical mastermind. Explosive shootouts, dangerous liaisons and cinematic qualities bring this story to life! Created, written and penciled by Tony Daniel (X-Force, Spawn, The Tenth, Adrenalynn), this giant sized debut issue is sure to please all! 48 pages of heart pounding excitement and adventure, in full color. Features a special pull out poster!

The high-octave excitement continues in May as the F5 crew find out how alone they are in a world of double-crossing spies and secret weapons. They uncover that the president of a German Bio-Development company will stop at nothing to attain the world's newest entry into the "weapons of mass destruction" list. Penny and the rest of F5 must find and secure this deadly new substance and return it to its rightful owners...the U.S. Airforce! There's no room for mistakes now! It's life or death in F5! Wall to wall action, jam packed with characters you care about. F5 the MUST SEE book of 2000! 32 pages, full color by Image Comics. Created, written and penciled by Tony Daniel, Inks by Rich Bonk and Kevin Conrad, colors by Steve Firchow.

The world has never been as unstable and unsafe now that Kessler, a German billionaire, has acquired the world's newest and most lethal weapon ever! With some key members of F5 MIA, will the short-handed Penny be able to put a stop to Kessler's crazed and diabolical antics before it's too late? Follow Penny and the rest of F5 into Europe as they try to close-in on this mastermind of destruction!

As the web of lies and deceit begin to unravel, F5 learns their true fate. Penny and the rest of F5 discover that there is more than one party interested in Kessler's new weapon of mass destruction! The last leg of their first mission becomes lethal as the team is betrayed by one of their own, and a team member dies. Penny wants revenge---on the double agent! Find out who the double agent is! Illustrated and written by creator, Tony Daniel, inks by Rich Bonk and Colors by Steve Firchow.

Finally available through comics shops, Dark Horse presents a brand-new edition of the hard-to-find F5 Origin one-shot special, originally available only through Fandom.com. Featuring an exclusive story not included in the original F5 series from Image Comics, a brand-new wraparound cover by Tony Daniel, and new character-profile pages, this special edition is sure to excite Tony Daniel fans old and new. No F5 collection is complete without this issue, don't miss out!

Overview

Bruno is a human on the run on the alien planet Thera. Detective Alia Sparrow, head of the planet's Human Crimes Unit, sympathetically hides Bruno away in the underground, where he meets and befriends a legendary samurai. But when a powerful foe learns of Sparrow's treason, he send a squad of hellhounds to locate and kill her!
name: All Roads Lead To (New) Rome Part 3

description: In just 12 hours, Bruno will become a deadly walking plague that will wipe out the entire human population on Planet Thera. Alia Sparrow, head of Thera's Human Crimes Bureau, has a horrible decision to make: Should she destroy him and save all of humankind? Or invade the inner core of the evil geneticist Crucifer's laboratory to find the vaccine that can save him? The answer won't be an easy one, and will push Sparrow and her partner Greta to the brink of their friendship!
name: All Roads Lead to (New) Rome Part 4

description: It's all been building up to this: Bruno is an unwilling "Trojan Horse," carrier of a virus from planet Thera that could wipe out the entire population of Earth! Alia Sparrow, head of Thera's Human Crimes Bureau, has the weight of two worlds on her back: Should she destroy Bruno and save all of humankind? Or find the genetic cure that can save him by invading the laboratory of the evil geneticist Crucifer?
name: All Roads Lead to (New) Rome Part 5

description: The rumors are true: comics superstar Tony Daniel is now at Dark Horse! As the acclaimed former artist of Spawn and X-Force and the best-selling creator of The Tenth, Adrenalynn, and F5, Daniel is renowned among fans and professionals alike for the explosive dynamism of his visuals and the innovative excitement of his creations. And his latest and greatest creation is about to be unleashed: Silke. When a secret CIA experiment goes wrong, the participants find their genetic structures altered, giving them enhanced abilities and the power to morph their appearances. But the project gets shut down with extreme prejudice! and one of the participants, Sandra Silke, escapes?and now she's been framed for the murder of the other transformed agents and has become a fugitive who must set things right at all costs! Silke is the action-packed story of one woman's battle for survival against overwhelming odds, and is created, written, and drawn by Tony Daniel. Don't miss your chance to get in on the ground floor of the hot new series of 2001!
name: Playing God

description: Sandra Silke returns home to find out she's been framed for the murder of her dead CIA comrades, and as news footage showing her committing horrific murders streams across the airwaves and newspapers all over the country, she discovers that the only way for her to clear her name is to confront and expose the people responsible for her shape-shifting powers. But a souped-up predator by the name of Nathan is on the hunt for her, and he won't stop until she's dead! As her world becomes more and more surreal, Silke realizes that can't stay in hiding forever... Can she keep a cool head and survive? Don't miss a single chapter of this incredible story!
name: The Chameleon

description: THE HUNT IS ON! Nathan Spinter and his henchmen, enhanced with synthetic DNA, use Sandra's own blood to track her. Sandra's trail leads them to Brigit, a woman very similar to Sandra. Brigit has morphed herself into a supermodel for the last year and has been living the good life -- that is, until Sandra and Jason show up at her mansion gate! They soon realize that the country's security is at stake as Spinter plans a "body-snatching" assassination plot against the President of the United States! Sandra is reluctant but must make the right choice. But to do so will mean the ultimate sacrifice! The excitement comes to a head in the third installment of Silke,Tony Daniel's latest blockbuster hit! Intense story, hot art, and two sizzling covers! Holy cow!
name: Blood and Bullets

description: Morphing, killer shapeshifters, a Presidential assassination plot, world domination ... Silke #4 has it all! Silke, the all-new monthly miniseries by Tony Daniel is most likely the hottest action series of the new year! Silke, the hot, young CIA operative whose life has been turned upside down and inside out by a secret research laboratory, must use the horrors that she holds within to overcome the evil forces that threaten world security. Sandra decides that she has to do the right thing and infiltrate Nathan Spinter's death squad in order to thwart a Presidential Assassination plot. But will her morphing skills be enough to fight the mutant hunter that has finally tracked her down? Sandra will be backed into a corner and it's do or die! Find out what so many people are screaming about in the latest issue of Silke!
name: A Hostile Takeover

description:
DC's hottest new teams collide in an explosive one-shot! Following the events of "The Insiders"crossover, a villain from the Titans' past returns with a plan for revenge on former Titans! Plus, what's the deal with the crazy Titan who calls herself the Joker's Daughter?

I Am Donna Troy- While on New Cronus, Donna looks in on what the Teen Titans and the Outsiders have done since her death.

Teen Titan Hunt-Robin and Starfire have been kidnapped from The Tower, and Nightwing, Arsenal and Beast Boy try to find them. This leads to the discovery of a Wildebeest Society clone, and the fact that Cyborg was kidnapped also. After defeating the clone, with some help from Grace and Jade, Nightwing and Starfire discuss the two teams working together again.

Who's Your Daddy?- While on the old Injustice Gang Satellite, which is now a bar for villains, Duela is confronted by other villains to who her true father is. Duela leaves them all with more questions then answers.

Secrets- Wonder Girl and Arrowette discuss the Secret to who Wonder Girl's father is and if she should tell the Teen Titans. This leads into the fact that Superboy has turned evil.

description: In Japan the C.I.A. special OPS are in a frenzy as the supermonster Gozza is killing off entire towns, turning them to villages of blackness. Elsewhere, the Tenth, Zorina and Esperanza are searching for clues to the identity of Blackspell. While searching the condo of Zorina's mother they come across a telecommunications device with a direct link up to a Director Jaffe. Was Zorina's mother a covert agent in a plot to uncover the pans of Rhazes Darkk? A question that goes unanswered as a new Supermonster calling himself Lastic enters and in his assault, knocks Victor 15 stories down, triggering his transformation.

After falling 15 stories Victor has transformed into the Tenth to battle Lastic. After being taunted into a free attack towards Lastic, the Tenth learns that Lastic has a new power. He can now twist reality, and sapped away the Tenth's monster form and reduces Victor to his normal self. With the help of Zorina and Esperanza, they all escape. In Tokyo, after a hit Yuri says goodbye to Adrenalynn as he gives her services over to a new benefactor named Moto Fujisaki. In an Illinois cemetery the Tenth, Zorina and Espy try to devise a plan to save Zorina"s mom from Blackspell when the supermonster Gulliver teleports into a nearby grave.

Rhazes Darkk has returned, awakening the supermonster Gozza in a dark vision. Gozza awaits his confrontation with his hated creator.The Tenth, Esperanza and Zorina make a deal with the supermonster Gulliver to be teleported inside the body of Blackspell in return for their service in defeating Rhazes Darkk. In Tokyo, Moto Fujisaki is preparing Adrenalynn by erasing her memory implants and redirecting her to kill the 10 supermonsters, starting with Gozza.

Zorina finds her mother, but not believing it to be real, punches her in the face. Esperanza battles demons and the Tenth is pissed at Gulliver for teleporting the three of them to separate locations. The Tenth is suddenly attacked by Rhazes Darkk and his three companions, leading to a fight. After defeating the monsters, Espy searches for her cat Arusa, when Blackspell rises from beneath her. Blackspell is hit with a powerful blast from the Tenth to save his friends. The Tenth asks for a drop of Espy's blood in order to subside his fury. Meanwhile Zorina's mother explains to her daughter how deep she was into Rhazes Darkk's experiments and the deal from Director Jaffe to help undo Darkk's madness. Her mom vanishes as Gulliver teleports them all right in front of Gozza. In a chicago morgue Lastic appears and kills several people until he gets torched and taken away by the people posing as C.D.C. In Tokyo, Moto Fujisaki readies Adrenalynn to take on Gozza.
